        "id": 1000000
      },
      "writtenOn": "2026-04-24T02:04:27Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Isn\u0027t this a very heavy hammer though?  It means we _never_ get a NotReady even if it might be a true condition ...\n\nTo recap/clarify:\n- If bmc-state-manager starts before multi-user.target completes, we emit NotReady and then Ready.  This seems ok.\n- If bmc-state-manager starts as multi-user.target complets, we emit only Ready.  This is also ok even though \"inconsistent\".\n- If the BMC is in the process of rebooting, due to a user requires, I would not expect any new event to happen as part of that reboot except maybe an [new?] explicit \"Rebooting\" state.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 22,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 25,
        "endChar": 54
      },
      "revId": "11988f7cb3367e3e1c01e58df197511cf45fdc6a",
